(263, 1, '2015-09-21 11:52:03', '2015-09-21 11:52:03', 'Obtaining permission to use a protected work requires entering into an agreement with the owner of that work. Your agreement may give you the right to use the work (a "license"). Before you contact a rights holder to obtain the necessary permissions, you should have a clear idea of how you intend to incorporate the other’s work and what you intend to do with your project.\r\n\r\nLicensing is a common method for obtaining rights. These are simply contracts between you and the work’s copyright owner that grant you permission to use the work according to the terms of the license.', 'Permission and License', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'permission-and-license', '', '', '2015-09-21 11:52:03', '2015-09-21 11:52:03', '', 0, 'http://52.5.189.130/?post_type=cpt_discography&#038;p=263', 0, 'cpt_discography', '', 0),
